                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="20102" author="adrian.colyer" created="Thu, 5 Oct 2006 20:43:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug was caused by the recent fix to ReflectiveMethodInvocation to ensure that all interceptors get driven correctly when proceeding multiple times in an advice body. The userAttributes map was not properly cloned (not initialised early enough), causing binding information to be placed in one map, but looked up in another one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue only affects advice binding when multiple interceptors are used at the same join point (so basic binding tests in the AOP suite did not pick it up).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20103" author="adrian.colyer" created="Thu, 5 Oct 2006 20:55:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;tests and fix now committed in tree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
